properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 10 at 6:48PM CST until January 11 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Topeka KS
properties.description:
...Difficult Travel Conditions Tonight through Saturday Afternoon...

A complex winter system will continue to impact the region
through the day tomorrow. A light wintry mix is expected this
evening before a brief lull in precipitation occurs tonight.
Another batch of winter weather is then expected to move in
tomorrow morning, mainly across eastern Kansas. Tomorrow's round
of weather will be all snow and could fall moderate to heavy at
times during the morning.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation. A light dusting of snow and light
glaze of ice are possible. Winds gusting as high as 40 mph.

* WHERE...Portions of central, east central and northeast Kansas.

* WHEN...The precipitation will come to an end by midnight
tonight, if not sooner. Light snow is also possible on Saturday,
but impacts look to be low.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions through the overnight
hours. The strong winds and freezing rain may result in a few
tree limbs breaking and isolated power outages.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
